Hands on practice 30 min:

A) Make sure that all have docker installed
B) Make sure that all have Docker hub account

1) show version: Docker version
2) Run alpine container: docker run -it alpine /bin/ash
3) Disconnect from the container: ctrl p + q
4) Attach to the container: docker attach ID
5) Run a command in a container: docker exec ID cat /etc/passwd
6) Show containers: docker ps
7) Show all containers: docker ps -a
8) Show images: docker images
9) Inspect container: docker inspect ID
10) Stop container: docker stop ID
11) start containerL docker start ID
12) Show logs: docker logs ID
13) Kill container: docker kill ID
14) Delete container: docker rm ID
15) Delete Image: docker rmi ID
